00040   string getFileContents(const string& conffile)
00041   {
00042     struct stat b;
00043     if(stat(conffile.c_str(),&b)<0)
00044       {
00045   cerr << "Cannot stat() file " << conffile << endl;
00046   abort();
00047       }
00048     
00049     fstream ist(conffile.c_str());
00050     if(!ist)
00051       {
00052   cerr << "Could not open file " << conffile << endl;
00053   abort();
00054       }
00055     
00056     string rc(b.st_size,' ');
00057     ist.getline(&rc[0],b.st_size,fstream::traits_type::eof());
00058     return rc;
00059   }
00060 }

00107 void Drain::readData()
00108 {
00109   while(1)
00110     {
00111       DR_DEBUG << "Drain: getting event" << endl;
00112       std::auto_ptr<edm::EventPrincipal> ep = ext_.extract();
00113       DR_DEBUG << "Drain: got event " << (void*)ep.get() << endl;
00114       // if(ep.release()==0) break;
00115       if(ep.get()==0) break;
00116       ++count_;
00117     }
00118 
00119   cout << "Drain: got " << count_ << " events" << endl;

00204 int Main::run()
00205 {
00206   cerr << "starting the collector and drain" << endl;
00207   drain_.start();
00208   coll_->start();
00209   //coll2_.start();
00210   cerr << "started the collector and drain" << endl;
00211   // sleep(10);
00212 
00213   // start file readers
00214   Readers::iterator it(readers_.begin()),en(readers_.end());
00215   for(;it!=en;++it)
00216     {
00217       (*it)->start();
00218     }
00219   cerr << "started readers" << endl;
00220   // wait for all file readers to complete
00221   for(it=readers_.begin();it!=en;++it)
00222     {
00223       (*it)->join();
00224     }
00225   cerr << "readers done" << endl;
00226 
00227   // send MsgCode::DONE to the drain
00228   // jbk - this is broken now - it only sends a null
00229   edm::EventBuffer::ProducerBuffer b(info_.getFragmentQueue());
00230   b.commit();
00231   //edm::EventBuffer::ProducerBuffer b2(info_.getFragmentQueue());
00232   edm::EventBuffer::ProducerBuffer b2(info_.getEventQueue());
00233   b2.commit();
00234 
00235   cerr << "waiting for coll to be done" << endl;
00236   coll_->join();
00237   cerr << "coll done" << endl;
00238   cerr << "waiting for drain to be done" << endl;
00239   //coll2_.join();
00240   drain_.join();
00241   cerr << "drain done" << endl;
00242   return 0;
00243 }
